From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VPS Builder <build@vps.local>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] compat: include linux/compat before fallback syscall macro

On x86_64 Android 6.1, <asm/compat.h> provides in_compat_syscall and defines a
marker macro with the same name. ReSukiSU's fallback macro can be defined before
<linux/compat.h> is included, causing the later x86 inline function declaration
to be parsed through the fallback function-like macro.

Include <linux/compat.h> first so the kernel-provided implementation is visible
before the fallback guard is evaluated.
---
 kernel/compat/kernel_compat.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/kernel/compat/kernel_compat.h b/kernel/compat/kernel_compat.h
index 5e8786f..067d642 100644
--- a/kernel/compat/kernel_compat.h
+++ b/kernel/compat/kernel_compat.h
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@
 #include <linux/fs.h>
 #include <linux/version.h>
 #include <linux/fdtable.h>
+#include <linux/compat.h>
 #include "ss/policydb.h"
 #include "linux/key.h"
 
